cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper proposes a novel deep learning model for multivariate time series data with missing values. The model is based on recurrent neural networks and utilizes missing patterns to improve prediction performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses real-world clinical datasets, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
